{"type":"message","id":"46b2cdd9","parentId":"235e9b1d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:11:34.379Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6upjo7vkscbl_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 021114\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/TIC-SPEC.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n2. A major insight has been synthesized: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n3. The next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n\r\nThe pending action clearly states:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe immediate next action should be to implement the TIC classifier. This would likely be a script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse log files\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant or variant\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse content\r\n4. Reports metrics\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC experiment script. This is a concrete, specific action that advances the goals.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight provides a clear experimental path: implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) to test whether causal structure discovery and compression are the same problem. The success criteria are defined (>70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic_experiment.ps1` - a PowerShell script that reads pulse logs, classifies content as invariant (stable across sessions) vs variant (changes), and attempts next-pulse prediction from invariants. This directly tests the core hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure.\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:11:26\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774332694378}}
{"type":"message","id":"10129407","parentId":"46b2cdd9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:11:40.868Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse completed successfully. Let me summarize the result.","thinkingSignature":"07f4725dfa0b6ef8ab8923661c0219aa7138e3f13687eee541c7c279a0c80ebe"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse (2:11 AM ET) — Complete ✅**\n\n**Insight generated:** COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY — a key theoretical synthesis from the COMPOSER project. The hypothesis: causal structure discovery and compression are the same problem. Invariant content (stable across sessions) = causal structure.\n\n**Next action queued:** Implement a TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier — a script that reads pulse logs, separates invariant vs variant content, and attempts to predict the next pulse from invariants. Success criteria: >70% classification accuracy, >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy.\n\n**No mutations were applied** this cycle — the system is still in the planning/synthesis phase. The project appears to be converging toward an experiment to validate the core insight."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1037,"output":171,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13162,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774332694380}}
